Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.44,0:08:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I realized, Tsukihi's case was definitely strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.00,0:08:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Up until this point, Araragi Tsukihi is the only one that seems normal. Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.84,0:08:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I need information on my present situation if I want to revise my strategy going forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.52,0:08:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so I thought I should go to a bookstore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.76,0:08:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Why a bookstore you might ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.27,0:08:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, when I saw Black Hanekawa's body I was filled with desire and went to buy a porno mag
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.20,0:09:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is of course not the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.00,0:09:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the real world I may not have many friends but,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.37,0:09:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to historical figures, as my test results show,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.45,0:09:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I more or less know what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.75,0:09:10.35,Road,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\alpha&H255&}{\fry180}{\move(960,40,950,1200,0,600)}Taira no Kiyomori
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.55,0:09:12.09,Road,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\alpha&H255&}{\fry180}{\move(960,40,950,1200,0,540)}Minamoto no Yoritomo
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.26,0:09:13.81,Road,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\alpha&H255&}{\fry180}{\move(960,40,950,1200,0,550)}Toyotomi Kunimatsu
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.97,0:09:15.60,Road,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\alpha&H255&}{\fry180}{\move(960,40,950,1200,0,630)}Tokugawa Ieyasu
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.73,0:09:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought there was book of accounts regarding one of them,\N{I have no idea what this was referring to, it's tho best I can do} with a section called "Why Humans are Being Reversed."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.22,0:09:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{Sign}{\pos(960,75)}{\fry180}歴史書 = History book
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:20.65,Monowall W,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1680,250)}{\frz7}{\fry180}{\fscx130\fscy130\b0}HISTORY
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:20.65,Monowall W,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1130,187)}{\frz6}{\fry180}{\fscx140\fscy140\b0}GEOGRAPHY
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.70,0:09:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(960,75)}{\fry180}歴史 = History
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.36,0:09:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,However, becase of the previous theory, this train of thought struck out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.00,0:09:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just spinning my wheels, the search was completely meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.80,0:09:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the written charactes were flipped left to right, I couldn't read them at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.46,0:09:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,, I tried as much as I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.02,0:09:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Deciphering each character one by one wasn't that hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.16,0:09:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it came to the meaning of a sentence it was too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.84,0:09:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My brain couldn't process it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.50,0:09:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon after that, I gave up on that approach all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.33,0:09:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I head back to Kita-shirahebi shrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.27,0:09:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.83,0:09:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hachikuji-oneesan won't be back yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.66,0:09:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, before I meet up with her again
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there's another challenge or two I need to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.26,0:09:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.00,0:10:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to meet with that impudent stuffed girl doll enshrined in my sisters room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to speak with that specialist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.70,0:10:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh, it's just Koyomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.41,0:10:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You startled me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.80,0:10:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This voice, I feel like I remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.51,0:10:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's different, from the first thing she said the nuance was different
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Like it's covering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.28,0:10:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm? What is it, Koyomi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.77,0:10:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren't you coming in?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.12,0:10:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-This oppressive feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.29,0:11:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My body remembers it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.60,0:11:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmmm, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.57,0:11:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering where you went, Koyomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.27,0:11:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the bookstore?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.33,0:11:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems you brought another lewd book back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.59,0:11:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you couldn't help yourself! {shouganai}{clearly this can't be helped}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She knows?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.49,0:11:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.15,0:11:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already been living under the same roof with a girl this cute for 10 years already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.41,0:11:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really okay with a book? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.74,0:11:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We already feel like family though, so I guess nothing can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.33,0:11:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We already feel like family?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.13,0:11:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey now, Koyomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.86,0:11:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're looking forward to your porn magazine but,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.23,0:11:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting here bored and alone all by myself so let's have a cup of tea together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.14,0:11:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only proper to have cake with tea and I have a good math puzzle ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.66,0:11:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit, why can't I resist her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.41,0:11:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't oppose her at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.27,0:11:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what you do against this girl, it's like you naturally can't resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.77,0:11:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that voice, but I can't think of who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.06,0:11:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Math puzzle?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.02,0:12:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! You're Oikura Sodachi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.77,0:12:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh! You scared me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.84,0:12:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been living in this house together since elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.61,0:12:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What's gotten into you Koyomi?
Comment: 0,0:12:16.06,0:12:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,010
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.82,0:12:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.62,0:12:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this puzzle amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.58,0:12:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So is this one, and aren't I too for solving it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.37,0:12:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Even thought it was really hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.50,0:12:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.39,0:12:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you use this diagram the answer is obvious!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.75,0:12:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that cool?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.67,0:12:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe we solved so many in one go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.47,0:12:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Is that so, Sodachi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.17,0:12:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As expected from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.66,0:12:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm impressed you could solve so many problems that hard, I'm proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Koyomi praised me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.97,0:12:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.46,0:12:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.13,0:12:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it Koyomi? Your face is red.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.46,0:12:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you catch a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.90,0:12:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The temperature seemed normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey Sodachi, your favorite mathematician is Euler, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.09,0:13:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ehh? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.08,0:13:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Euler was a great mathematician, but my personal favorite is Gauss.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.21,0:13:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You should know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.24,0:13:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,These differences are too difficult for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.66,0:13:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Has she really been mirrored?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.57,0:13:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me your tea for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.52,0:13:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,An indirect kiss from Koyomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.18,0:13:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're amazing Koyomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.38,0:13:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You solved all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.46,0:13:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though my grades are better, when it comes to this type of thing I'm no match.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.94,0:13:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't mean I don't like it or that it's painful for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.02,0:13:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sodachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.96,0:13:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This feeling, it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.81,0:13:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's always been this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.40,0:13:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but I want it always to be like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.50,0:14:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.88,0:14:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.60,0:14:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Koyomi-chan's here. Karen-chan's here. Tsukihi-chan's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.54,0:14:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom and Dad are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.55,0:14:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is kind to me and we get along well like a proper family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.58,0:14:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm truly happy like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.18,0:14:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.88,0:14:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel{\alpha&HFF&} like all of this is a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.16,0:14:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like all of this is a lie.
Comment: 0,0:14:27.95,0:14:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,011
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.62,0:14:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside my sister's room, Ononki Yotsugi was nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.13,0:14:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if her posed look annoys me and she has that bratty tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.42,0:14:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ononoki-chan is still Ononoki-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.81,0:14:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Even imperfect, she's still a specialist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.09,0:14:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that, if there was something that happened to her, I still need to see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.76,0:14:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The loose plan I had come up with was falling apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.93,0:14:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I still have no idea what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.01,0:14:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But, when I look back on my prior experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.22,0:15:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I still didn't know if what's happening now is necessarily a bad thing or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.20,0:15:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This world certainly isn't coherent with a normal "Mirror World."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.33,0:15:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't the most reasonable explanation that it could be the product of some oddity's realization?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.16,0:15:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yahoo! Araragi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.21,0:15:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Mayoi-oneesan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.47,0:15:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,With a face like that, it looks like you've had nothing but bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.69,0:15:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't worry! There's still hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,For Arargi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.13,0:15:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx150\fscy150}For Arargi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.49,0:15:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fscx250\fscy250}For Arargi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.65,0:15:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I used my connections and called on a realiable helper!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.41,0:15:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}SHA SHA SHA SHA
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.50,0:15:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Greetings Koyomi-oniichan. It is I!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.53,0:15:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while hasn't it, how are you faring since last we met?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.79,0:15:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sengoku Nadewho-san?
Comment: 0,0:15:47.95,0:15:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,012
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.05,0:15:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}SHA SHA SHA!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.68,0:15:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you already know her but, since you did come from another world you might not so
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.09,0:15:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll introduce her anyways, Arargi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.27,0:15:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.93,0:16:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Or rather, the previous generation's God: Kuchinawa-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.96,0:16:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}Haaa
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.37,0:16:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}SHA SHA!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.32,0:16:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it, you're constantly overthinking everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.50,0:16:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as the cat said.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.23,0:16:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.29,0:16:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell was that? That wink was awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.57,0:16:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahhhhh? What is it Koyomi-oniichan?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.50,0:16:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't understand what I'm saying? Too much for you to follow?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.64,0:16:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.42,0:16:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}SHA SHA!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.77,0:16:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't glare at me like that. I didn't just come here to tease you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.93,0:16:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have you know that for a time I was the one enshrined here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.57,0:16:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it was because that cat helped. {N: yeah I dunno}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.31,0:16:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.83,0:16:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.34,0:16:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the serious face?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.96,0:16:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't she just say that you overthink things too much?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.42,0:17:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be that you didn't come to a "Mirror World" at all so
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.62,0:17:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,now I'm looking forward to having some fun, with this boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.44,0:17:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. {N: I understand/get it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.17,0:17:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Any help would be great. {N: Just felt right}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.16,0:17:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}Ahhhhh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.06,0:17:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that a request I just heard? {N: I dunno but sounds wrong}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.04,0:17:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well since I am a God and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.99,0:17:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Or rather because it's me you're asking, \NI can resolve what you've been thinking about. {N: Uhg}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.54,0:17:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.20,0:17:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuchinawa-san will be super reliable here, Araragi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.67,0:17:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes to helpful gods, right now Kuchinawa-san is the best that could come!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.32,0:17:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of all the gods she's the best?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.61,0:17:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.78,0:17:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because, if it's snakes you're talking about she's the expert.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.14,0:17:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.37,0:17:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Araragi-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.29,0:17:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The word "mirror" comes from the term snake-eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.35,0:17:47.28,Monowall R,,0,0,0,,{\pos(950,700)\b1}Mirror\NSnake-eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.60,0:17:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Or mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.54,0:17:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you know that?
Comment: 0,0:17:49.56,0:17:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,013
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.44,0:17:51.66,Monowall B,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(960,660)\b1}{\fry180}Of course I didn't know that {me neither}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.17,0:17:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you hungry Araragi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.40,0:17:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we're talking and you haven't eaten anything since morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.05,0:17:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we eat while we talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.73,0:18:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You too Kuchinawa-san, drink up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.26,0:18:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyways, isn't this food shrine offerings?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.26,0:18:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup, they're offerings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.53,0:18:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Koyomi-oniichan, you think the mirror reversed everything left to right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.78,0:18:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.95,0:18:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When I raise my right hand the mirrored left hand rises
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.51,0:18:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I raise my left foot the right foot rises, is how I think it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.19,0:18:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You really think that's how it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because that's how everyone says it is, doesn't mean that's the only way to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.52,0:18:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuchinwa-san, is it actually different from that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.21,0:18:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think Hachikuji-oneesan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.17,0:18:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's state my opinion at the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.51,0:18:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's continue Kuchinawa's thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.99,0:18:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Kuchinawa-san. If the mirror isn't reflecting the world from left to right,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.79,0:19:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Just how is it reflecting it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.07,0:19:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.90,0:19:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Since times immemorial, and in the way we're using it in this conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.83,0:19:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A mirror has been a tool for spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.41,0:19:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Reflecting reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.78,0:19:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No, those words in themselves present problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.91,0:19:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So what should I say instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.79,0:19:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of lesson should I take from this conversation anyways?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.20,0:19:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahhh, you still don't understand, Koyomi-oniichan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.26,0:19:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If I look at it from you're point of view this world might even be mirrored left to right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.90,0:19:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But is just mirroring it really a reversal? Isn't it correct either way?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.96,0:19:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Both are{\alpha&HFF&} correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.21,0:19:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Both are correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.66,0:19:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.02,0:19:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyways when you bring it all together, everyone you know is still in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.76,0:19:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Your sisters, friends, kouhai, childhood friend, even Mayoi-oneesan and me, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.52,0:19:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't necessarily mean the world is reversed left to right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.33,0:20:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you starting to understand now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.18,0:20:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, it wasn't mirrored.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.27,0:20:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We are presented properly as we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.28,0:20:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we're a mirrored image, we're not an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.21,0:20:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}SHA SHA
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.39,0:20:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I could tell from the way your eyes read me earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.33,0:20:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The me that Koyomi-oniichan knows and this me are completely different,\N even though you may think we're the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.61,0:20:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately, this is also me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.28,0:20:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Sengoku Nadeko.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.02,0:20:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's return to our earlier conversation Koyomi-oniichan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.91,0:20:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take what Koyomi-oniichan said and raise your right hand,\n your left hand rises because it's an image mirrored left to right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.81,0:20:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In this example it wouldn't matter if you're a snake that doesn't have arms or legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.34,0:20:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the case of a snake how would you think of mirroring left to right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.04,0:20:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}Umm
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.99,0:20:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.00,0:20:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like the shape of scales or how things are lined up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously, think about it like a snake you idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.60,0:20:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you explain the idea of left to right reversal\N to someone that has no concept of left and right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.26,0:21:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.81,0:21:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, wouldn't the reflection of a character work?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.40,0:21:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(950,75)}{\fry180}SHA SHA
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.32,0:21:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A character?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.88,0:21:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In the alphabet there's a lot of left to right symmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.60,0:21:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So would like hiragana, katakana, or kanji be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.94,0:21:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you reflect those left and right become reversed, \Nso that should be able to explain how a mirror reverses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.72,0:21:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.16,0:21:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So Koyomi-oniichan, what the next step?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.20,0:21:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still more?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.35,0:21:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, this is the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.56,0:21:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,After this you can hear Mayoi-oneesan's opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.65,0:21:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,75)}{\fry180}Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.61,0:21:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose that there's a new situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.83,0:21:38.05,Monowall B,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(1200,540)\b1}{\fry180}Araragi Koyomi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.21,0:21:40.44,Monowall B,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(550,540)\b1}{\fry180}Araragi Koyomi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.95,0:21:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say you are shown "Araragi-Koyomi" reversed in a mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.57,0:21:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have "Araragi-Koyomi" reversed written on a piece of paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.59,0:21:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What do think?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.05,0:21:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well if it's mirrored writing, that seems normal doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.80,0:21:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's say you don't know about mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.11,0:21:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, you wouldn't know about mirror writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.34,0:21:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure let's say I don't know what mirror writing is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.53,0:22:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I wouldn't know those words, I would describe it as being being reversed left to right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.01,0:22:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, that's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.82,0:22:12.71,Monowall Y,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,75)}{\fry180}Kita-Shirahebi Shrine
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.15,0:22:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I typically only associate mirroring with being reversed from left to right \Nwhen I'm actually in front of a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.92,0:22:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm in something like a big bookstore,\N for example when I try to read history books.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.07,0:22:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.48,0:22:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When I tried to look at the other side of the page from the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.35,0:22:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That time it was a failure, but on the paper it was written in mirror writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.89,0:22:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,75)}{\fry180}Seamless Typesetting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.80,0:22:25.20,Monowall B,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(490,670)\b1}{\fry180}{\frz50}{\fscx200\fscy200}Dream
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.20,0:22:26.52,Monowall B,,0,0,0,,{sign}{\pos(700,780)\b1}{\frz310}{\fscx200\fscy200}Dream
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.46,0:22:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, the page is flipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.53,0:22:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, if the mirror isn't reversing from left to right then,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.12,0:22:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,People are being flipped inside out to a different side of themselves.
Comment: 0,0:22:31.12,0:22:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,(tl note if you're willing to put them in, 裏返す here means both to be flipped over and to be turned inside out)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.43,0:22:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,75)}Eureka!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.03,0:22:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.32,0:22:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When I came to this world, at first I thought I understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.80,0:22:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided already when I saw those girls that they were mirrored left to right images of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.73,0:22:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But those girls were flipped to show a different side.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.26,0:22:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, their inner-self is showing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.05,0:22:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take off her outer layers, she is the only one that doesn't change.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.89,0:22:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That reason is because she's exactly how she says she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.39,0:22:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,At her core she isn't any different.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.02,0:22:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.15,0:23:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The place the surface of the mirror brought me to,{\alpha&HFF&} shows the insides of people instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.91,0:23:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The place the surface of the mirror brought me to, shows the insides of people instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.78,0:23:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,
